						               													<description>Welcome to &amp;quot;Speakeasy&amp;quot;, the thrilling board game that will transport you back to the roaring 1920s, during the era of Prohibition. In this game, you will take on the role of a savvy mobster, managing and operating your very own speakeasy in Manhattan.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But running a speakeasy is no easy task, and you'll need to use all of your cunning and resources to stay ahead of the competition. As you improve your establishment, gain reputation, and upgrade to more lavish speakeasies and even casinos, you'll attract the attention of the local mafia bosses.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To gain an edge over your rivals, you can associate with these mobsters and even attack and rob rum runners to gain valuable resources. You'll need to manage your cards carefully, placing your workers strategically to deliver illicit liquor and reach Manhattan's goals to earn income.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this worker placement and card management game, you'll need to hire thugs to help you take over Manhattan during this exciting and dangerous time. The game is designed for 1 to 4 players, and takes around 40 minutes to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The ultimate goal is simple: accumulate the most money and become the most successful mobster in the city. Do you have what it takes to rise to the top of the speakeasy scene and take over Manhattan during Prohibition? It's time to grab your fedora and find out in &amp;quot;Speakeasy&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
